# EasyPanel Docker Deploys

When working on Docker/EasyPanel deployment failures in this repo, first read:

`docs/DOCKER_EASYPANEL_PLAYBOOK.md`

Project defaults:

- Use `node:20-bookworm-slim`, not `node:20-alpine`.
- Install with `npm ci` in Docker.
- Keep the root `Dockerfile` and `apps/web/Dockerfile` synchronized.
- Missing native packages like `@rollup/rollup-linux-x64-gnu`, `lightningcss-linux-x64-gnu`, or `@tailwindcss/oxide-linux-x64-gnu` are usually npm optional dependency lockfile issues, not app-code bugs.
- If adding Linux native optional dependencies, regenerate `package-lock.json` with `npm install --package-lock-only --force`, then verify the lockfile contains a real `node_modules/<package>` entry.
